reviews.text: Near. My place and after revamp , many new food stall. Lor mee is special and western food is not bad. Indian food is reasonable , the YTF is fresh , chicken rice have curry version , duck rice normal . Mix rice , reasonable price . Used to do my meeting there but evening time , all the rich and famous come for the zi char , anchor tenant. Rong JI. Oh the new nasi lemak is special too ! Watch my updates on tiktok , @mcmodelsg .

Visited this coffeeshop for the first time. Spacious and well ventilated. Evening time might be warm due to sun set shinning into the place. Good variety or non-muslim food and only 1 -2 stall serving muslim options.

Note the this coffeeshop is located right inside Northstar Industrial building, so yes you need to drive in, drive around (pass rows of pre-school on ur left) and you will see a coffeeshop facing AMK Ave 5.

The Carpark cost me $4.55 for about 3 hours of parking.

Washroom available on site.

I work in the building. Canteen is much nicer after the revamp. So patronise almost everyday for my favourite teh-O.
Some of the food that I like:
1) Malay stall Lontong
2) Lor Mee
3) Prata & Briyani
4) Hokkien Mee from the Tze char stall ( they are famous for their claypot crab noodles)

Drinks stall currently having promo. $0.80 drink for Sunday 5am-5pm for dining in only. Good deal. So I normally sit there to drink one teh-o before I go back office.
24 hours kopitiam along amk ave 5. The yong tau foo is good, they used to be at the 2 storey buangkok food center

Curious this coffee shop. My first time here . Beer quite expensive here . the beer lady very friendly.. try out zichar was looking for the menu the zichar auntie so rude just take off my menu like I cant afford to eat that kind of face.. order two dishes just to try out taste normal nothing special..
